title: For Sale:  Volunteer Enterprises Commando MKIII - Tommy Gun
postcontent:
For sale is my Volunteer Enterprises Commando MKIII .45ACP carbine, a semi-auto rifle styled after an Auto Ordinance Tommy Gun. This gun is a late model, manufactured in 1975, making it one of the highest-quality and most reliable Commandos out there. It uses 30-round M3 Grease Gun mags, which are still cheap and plentiful on GunBroker - much cheaper than actual Thompson 20-round stick mags. The receiver, 16-inch barrel, compensator, and magazine have been recently refinished in DuPont Teflon black at a cost of $250, and look excellent. It also has the highly-desirable vertical foregrip. It has been thoroughly cleaned and lubed, and only 5 rounds have been fired since the refinish to ensure proper function. 

I am also including a spare lower receiver, which I had planned to refinish and convert to use a genuine Thompson wooden handgrip and trigger, as well as the mechanism required to convert the stock to a push-button release, again emulating a genuine Thompson. The wooden buttstock can be easily removed with two screws, and the gun is quite fun to shoot without the stock. I am also including two spare firing pins and two firing pin springs, very hard-to-get parts when you need them, and a spare ejector, ejector pin, and ejector spring. title: For Sale:  AR15 Familiarization Course
postcontent:
This course is for those who have bought an AR15 (or any other AR-type rifle), but know nothing on how to use it or maintain it. Per my time in the US Marine Corps I will be more than happy to teach you how to effectively and safely use your AR, as well as how to properly maintain it.
The course will go as long as needed by the individual student (up to 8 hours), and covers the following in order:
1) Nomenclature, fieldstripping, and proper maintenance procedures
2) Effective ranges, sight usage, and proper shooting fundamentals as well as combat mindset
3) Basic hand to hand combat techniques and dealing with jams
4) Legalities
5) Live fire practical application (optional)

By the end of this course you should be able to: field strip, clean, and lubricate your AR; properly use iron sights and other optics; use proper shooting fundamentals and techniques to fire with accuracy; know and perform basic hand to hand techniques using your AR; basic techniques to deal with jams; have an idea of your combat mindset and levels of force; and much more!

PLEASE READ! Do note that while I am offering this course I will screen any and all potential students beforehand, and if I do not feel warm and fuzzy with teaching any student: I have the right to refuse to teach that student this course! This is effective from the prescreening to any time in the course. Teaching bad guys isn't my style; never was and never will be. 
This course is made especially for those who intend to use their ARs as a home/self defense tool as well as a fun gun to plink with at the local range.


Since I am also a full-time college student the best day that I can do classes is on Sundays. I cannot do any live-fire during the course until a local range opens up on the weekends again which likely won't be for another month or two. Until then I'm open to doing the course without live fire. Also: ammunition is to be paid for at your own expense, especially if it's an oddball caliber (6.5 Grendel for instance). AR15 ammo in general (5.56mm and .223 Rem) is pretty hard to find and between my college schedule and everything else I do I simply don't have the time to go find ammunition for you (however I can provide online sources where I've last seen ammo for under $1 per round). I apologize for this and hopefully things will get better and ammo availability will be somewhat back to normal in the future without gouged prices.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger Mini-14 Factory Folder
location: Conway/Coastal Carolina, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
Looking to thin the herd a little, so I'll start with a wonderful gun that I just don't shoot.  This is a 184- serial Ruger Mini-14 blue .223 semi-automatic rifle with the original factory folding stock.  I hate when people use the term "rare", but if you know about these rifles you know they just didn't make a whole lot of them, so let's just say they're "slightly unusual" and very desirable.  It's in good-to-excellent shape, with very few if any problems in the bluing and only compression marks on the wood stock---no scratches.  The bore is bright and shiny, and it has the side-plate replacement to take a scope mount---I have a brand-new one available for an additional charge at my cost ($39), it's never been installed and is still in the plastic.  I will offer this gun for sale with 2 20rd magazines---I have more available as well as some 30 rd mags, so if you want to work something else out let me know.  One unusual thing about this rifle is that it has the police-issue V rear sight as opposed to the more usual rear peep sight---I'm not the original owner so I don't know if it came this way from the factory or if somebody changed it after buying, but it's a Ruger sight and it's more unusual than the normal peep, so I take it as an extra, not a detractor---according to Ruger, only by special order or a few police agencies did this sight get shipped as factory original.

As listed I want $1200 cash, or I'd be interested in trades for other slightly unusual/not everyday guns in great shape.  If you want to talk about other mags, etc please send me an offer, but don't waste my time with lowballs---regular wood stock Minis are bringing over $1000 now, and this is a lot more collectible, a lot cooler and a lot more fun to shoot and show you friends!
